OL,3,CThe history of steelmaking in Port
OL,4,CTalbot
OL,6,FTraditional steel production at Tata's
OL,7,Fgiant plant in Port Talbot will end on
OL,8,FMonday, 30 September, when the last
OL,9,Fblast furnace will close down before
OL,10,Fthe transition to a much greener way
OL,11,Fof making steel.
OL,13,FThe history of industry in Port Talbot
OL,14,Fdates back to 1253 when the Lord of
OL,15,FNorth Cornelly, Walter Lovel, granted
OL,16,Fthe monks of Margam Abbey the
OL,17,Fprivilege of extracting iron and lead
OL,18,Fores from his land.
OL,20,FHere's a look at the history of
OL,21,Fsteelmaking in Port Talbot:
