OL,3,CThe history of steelmaking in Port
OL,4,CTalbot
OL,6,F1717: Lord Mansel's Forge was in
OL,7,Fexistence by 1717.
OL,9,F1770: The English Copper Company set
OL,10,Fup a works at Taibach.
OL,12,F1820: The Margam Tinplate Works opened
OL,13,Fin Aberavon.
OL,15,F1837: Port Talbot docks open. The
OL,16,Fdocks, and subsequently the town, are
OL,17,Fnamed after the wealthy industrialist
OL,18,FTalbot family, who were the main
OL,19,Fbackers behind the project.
