OL,3,CThe history of steelmaking in Port
OL,4,CTalbot
OL,6,FIn 1906, the Port Talbot Steel Company
OL,7,F(PTSC) reopened the steelworks. A
OL,8,Flight plate mill was built at Port
OL,9,FTalbot and commissioned in September
OL,10,F1908, to enable the GRCWC a source of
OL,11,Fraw materials.
OL,13,F1908-1914: New open-hearth steel and
OL,14,Ftwo rolling mills were built at Port
OL,15,FTalbot.
