OL,3,CThe history of steelmaking in Port
OL,4,CTalbot
OL,6,F1914: The Port Talbot works' capacity
OL,7,Fwas expanded to 5,000 tonnes of steel
OL,8,Fa week thanks to increased orders for
OL,9,Fsteel plates for shipbuilding and
OL,10,Fboilers, in addition to its
OL,11,Ftraditional rail and section markets.
OL,13,F1917: Establishment of Margam
OL,14,Fsteelworks, with two blast furnaces, a
OL,15,Fcoke plant and an open-hearth
OL,16,Fsteelmaking shop.
OL,18,F1923-1926: Margam Iron and Steel opens.
