OL,3,CThe history of steelmaking in Port
OL,4,CTalbot
OL,6,F1967: The Steel Company of Wales is
OL,7,Fabsorbed into British Steel. Around
OL,8,Fthis time, the Abbey Works plant is
OL,9,Fthe biggest of its kind in Europe and
OL,10,Fthe largest single employer in Wales `
OL,11,Fdirectly employing about 20,000 people.
OL,13,F1970: Margam Coke Ovens, Blast Furnace
OL,14,F1 and 2 are shut down.
OL,16,F1978: The Port Talbot Hot Mill
OL,17,Fcelebrates production of 50million
OL,18,Ftonnes.
